This paper deals with wireless communication networks and their optimization, which falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses power allocation and channel capacity, which are topics in Information Theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions backhaul network constraints, which are relevant to Multimedia (cs.MM) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of non-ideal link capacities, which is a concern in Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
